
# ─── Doppler (recommended) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The only secret needed on the host — everything else comes from Doppler.
# Generate at: doppler.com → nanoclaw project → production → Service Tokens
DOPPLER_TOKEN=dp.st.production.xxxx

# Start NanoClaw via: doppler run --token=$DOPPLER_TOKEN -- npm start
# (so the host process also gets ANTHROPIC_API_KEY etc. from Doppler)

# GWS credential files are auto-generated inside each container at startup
# from Doppler secrets — no physical files needed on the host.

# ─── Local dev (fallback, no Doppler) ────────────────────────────────────────
# If DOPPLER_TOKEN is not set, NanoClaw reads secrets from this file directly.

# Anthropic auth — one of:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=...

# Google Workspace CLI — all 3 accounts (injected into containers)
# Run `gws auth login` then `gws auth export --unmasked > ~/.config/gws/creds-<account>.json` for each account.
# Paths use the container-internal location (/home/node/.config/gws/).
# GWS_CREDENTIALS_SLOTHLABS=/home/node/.config/gws/creds-slothlabs.json
# GWS_CREDENTIALS_GMAIL=/home/node/.config/gws/creds-gmail.json
# GWS_CREDENTIALS_INVOCAP=/home/node/.config/gws/creds-invocap.json
# GOOGLE_WORKSPACE_CLI_CREDENTIALS_FILE=/home/node/.config/gws/creds-slothlabs.json
